<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<!-- Include the head -->
<%- include('../partials/head.ejs', { title: 'Post (name) | PlacementHub', cssFiles: ['/styles/forumpages.css', '/styles/nav.css'], bootstrap: true, infolder: false  }) %>


<body>

<!-- Include the navbar -->
<%- include('../partials/nav.ejs', { currentPage: 'Post (name)', infolder: false }) %>


<main class="main">


    <div class="card">
        <!-- Post content (same as before) -->
        <div class="user-info">
          <img src="user-photo.jpg" alt="User Photo" class="user-photo" />
          <div class="user-details">
            <p class="user-name">John Doe</p>
            <p class="user-course">Computer Science</p>
          </div>
          <p class="post-date">October 16, 2024</p>
        </div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <p class="post-title">How to implement a login system in Node.js?</p>
        <div class="post-actions">
          <button class="upvote">Upvote</button>
          <button class="downvote">Downvote</button>
          <button class="comment">Comment</button>
        </div>
      
        <!-- Separator Line for Comments -->
        <div class="comment-separator">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
            <path d="M12 21c4.97 0 9-3.94 9-9s-4.03-9-9-9-9 4.03-9 9c0 2.53 1.11 4.89 3 6.57V19h12v-1.43c1.89-1.68 3-4.04 3-6.57 0-4.97-4.03-9-9-9s-9 4.03-9 9c0 4.97 4.03 9 9 9z"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
      
        <!-- Comments Header (Sorting Buttons) -->
        <div class="comments-header">
          <button>Top Comments</button>
          <button>Newest Comments</button>
        </div>
      
        <!-- First Comment -->
        <div class="reply-card">
          <div class="user-info">
            <img src="reply-user.jpg" alt="User Photo" class="user-photo" />
            <div class="user-details">
              <p class="user-name">Jane Smith</p>
              <p class="user-course">Software Engineering</p>
            </div>
            <p class="post-date">October 16, 2024</p>
          </div>
          <div class="divider"></div>
      
          <div class="reply-content">
            <p>This is a great question! I found Passport.js to be a really useful tool for implementing authentication in Node.js.</p>
            <!-- Comment Actions -->
            <div class="comment-actions">
              <button class="upvote">Upvote</button>
              <button class="downvote">Downvote</button>
              <button class="reply">Reply</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      
        <!-- Second Comment -->
        <div class="reply-card">
          <div class="user-info">
            <img src="reply-user2.jpg" alt="User Photo" class="user-photo" />
            <div class="user-details">
              <p class="user-name">Mike Lee</p>
              <p class="user-course">Data Science</p>
            </div>
            <p class="post-date">October 16, 2024</p>
          </div>
          <div class="divider"></div>
      
          <div class="reply-content">
            <p>I second this! Plus, using JWT for tokens works really well.</p>
            <!-- Comment Actions -->
            <div class="comment-actions">
              <button class="upvote">Upvote</button>
              <button class="downvote">Downvote</button>
              <button class="reply">Reply</button>
            </div>
          </div>
      
          <!-- Nested Reply -->
          <div class="reply-card indented-reply">
            <div class="user-info">
              <img src="reply-user3.jpg" alt="User Photo" class="user-photo" />
              <div class="user-details">
                <p class="user-name">Anna White</p>
                <p class="user-course">Cybersecurity</p>
              </div>
              <p class="post-date">October 16, 2024</p>
            </div>
            <div class="divider"></div>
      
            <div class="reply-content">
              <p>Agreed! Passport and JWT work great together for securing APIs.</p>
              <!-- Comment Actions -->
              <div class="comment-actions">
                <button class="upvote">Upvote</button>
                <button class="downvote">Downvote</button>
                <button class="reply">Reply</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
        </div>


</main>



<%- include('../partials/footer.ejs')%>

</body>


